Wynyard County, New South Wales is one of the 141 Cadastral divisions of New South Wales . It contains the city of Wagga Wagga . The Murrumbidgee River lies on the northern edge of the county, and the Tumut River on the eastern edge. Wynyard County was named in honour of Major-General Robert Henry Wynyard (1802-1864).
